---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

xzl: 
it seems without old_kernel=1, (default?) firmware will load and kernel will boot in EL2, at 0x80000;
    the firmware can be override with supplied armstub=XXXX
    this is what QEMU emulates

w/ old_kernel=1, the kernel will directly boot (w/o any firmware before it); boot in EL3 at 0x0


https://forums.raspberrypi.com/viewtopic.php?t=323977#p1938907

Why are the armstub files needed?

"With the "kernel_old=1" setting in config.txt you can boot in EL3. To be more compatible with the other RPi models I prefer to use the standard boot mode. There is no ARM stub and no config.txt needed and also on the RPi 4 a custom ARM stub must be loaded with Circle only, if the FIQ is used."

cf:
https://github.com/raspberrypi/tools/tree/master/armstubs
https://trustedfirmware-a.readthedocs.io/en/v2.9/plat/rpi3.html

