    will boot either "cleanall makeall", or reboot a few times,.... why???
    dcache problem???

    simple kernel "hello world" can boot eveery time. why

    ** emmc (sdcard) failed to init  if boot from uboot... why????
        all sdcard registers look identical though. 
        sd cmd failed immediately with "bad status"
        (cf sd_int) 
    maybe b/c clock setup by uboot?? (meanwhile uboot can do sd card fine, e.g. can save parameters... why


    cf uboot arch/arm/dts/bcm2837-rpi-3-b.dts
    ...
    /* SDHCI is used to control the SDIO for wireless */
    ...
    /* SDHOST is used to drive the SD card */

    also same file, &gpio{ .... } has full def

    CAUSE
    uboot bcm2835_sdhost.c
                * The 2835 has two SD controllers: The Arasan sdhci controller
            * (supported by the iproc driver) and a custom sdhost controller
            * (supported by this driver).
            *
            * The sdhci controller supports both sdcard and sdio.  The sdhost
            * controller supports the sdcard only, but has better performance.
            * Also note that the rpi3 has sdio wifi, so driving the sdcard with
            * the sdhost controller allows to use the sdhci controller for wifi
            * support.
            * 
            */
    so, uboot uses "sdhost" to drive the sd card. 
    and our kernel uses "sdhci". there must be some lingering effect, so that 
        our code using sdhci failed to communciate with the card

    it's not the card itself.. tried to power it down, unplug it and replug...
    no avail

    pin mux also seems right. (our code has it)
    Circle does NOT help  (it supports both. emmc.cpp & sdhost.cpp) but not 
    at the same time. (conditional compilation)
    reading the code also does not reveal anything suspicious. 

    and, a quick try with uboot + Circle leads to hang (so I cannot verify
    if Circle can reconfigure sdhci, after uboot configures SDhost)

    OVERALL, it was UNCELAR (also lack of documentation) how to switch between 
    the two SD controllers (sdhost, sdhci) at run time (they share the same set of
    pins, but changing GPIO pin mux AT RUN TIME does NOT help??)
        our code seems to properly configure the pins (function selection and pull up/down mode) 
    it is even UNCELAR whether can be done? (maybe yes? b/c Linux can boot from 
    uboot)???

